The first batch of Ukraine based Nigerians have arrived in Abuja, the federal capital territory (FCT). The Ukraine-based Nigerians arrived in the country on Friday morning. Max Air flight VM602 from Bucharest landed Abuja at about 7:10 AM with the next flight from Hungary currently being expected. US Top Diplomat Meets With NATO Chief On Russia-Ukraine Crisis APC Crisis Deepens As Buhari’s Imposition Of Adamu, Others Tears… According to a source, the federal government will give $100 each to the Ukraine returnees upon their arrival.